column1: Welcome to the memory game! In this game, you must learn which images go together.
You will see two images on the left and right side of the screen, like this.
Your job is to remember that these images go together.
You could link them through a story. For example, jessica alba likes books.
After you see the images, we will test your memory.
Get ready to see the images! Each pair will only last on the screen for a few seconds, so pay attention.
We'll first do a practice to get you familiar with the game.
When you're ready to start the practice, press space!
Great job! Now we will see how well you remember which images go together.
You will first see one image, like below. Your job is to recall the image that it was paired with when you see this image.
Here, you should recall the book.
Then, you will see 3 other images and your job is to select the correct image pair. Use the keys 'J', 'K', or 'L' to indicate your choice.
Here, you should press 'L' because the woman, Jessica Alba, was paired with the book.
This portion is timed. Respond quickly and think of your answer as soon as you see the first image.

These keyboard options will remain on the screen under each image as a reminder throughout the task. If you don't know the answer, take a guess. After you select your answer, you will then be shown the correct image. Re-study the image pairs because you will be tested again at the end.
First, we'll do a practice. Put your right hand on the keyboard and get ready to respond! When you're ready to start, press space.
